review_blob: I really enjoyed this beer. It should be sold in a 6 pack instead of a 4. Moderate  hopping for a double.  ---Rated via Beer Buddy for Android

I'm not much on coriander so it will reflect on this review. Cloudy cream head pour. Citrus and coriander. N oddly bitter saison buying liked the originality. Didn't taste any fruit more floral outlay. Not bad but not that great either. Will recommend to my coriander buds.

---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone

Poured black with tan head. No retention tight rim bubbles. Coffee slight smoke. High alcohol smell. Very similar to Young's. pretty good but had better. Would bump the IBU 's from 53 to mid 60's.

---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone

This is definitely a beer that I will buy again. Grapefruit, malty, very complex. I am going to try more selections from this brewer. Ibu's are right on spot at 65. For 7.2 abv I don't detect too much alcohol. Great brew for price.

---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone

This beer tastes like leftover pumpkin spice vat scrapins from fall pumpkin beers. Won't buy again. This brewer adds too many additives to this sad attempt to capture winter themes in a brew. I even tried to mask the taste with a hoppy favorite and lost even more. Brewer needs to stop the additives addiction. :(

---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone

I enjoyed this beer. Not too hoppy but has a complex fruity taste. Won best beer award in 2008 in St. Louis. Will buy again.

---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone
dark amber white head with tight nit bubbles. slight citrus and hoppy. great BW for price!

Bought bottle at the keg liqour store at $5.49/bottle. Good price for quality. Drank at 60 degrees. Poured dark amber with light amber tight nit bubbles the lingered for a long while. Strong winey taste but no killer notes. Very good beer.

This is an excellent OTC beer. Thought it might resemble their flagship brews at first but I was shocked! This beer is very bitter for an OTC but still remains tastefully complex. I will buy this beer again!

Sweet in the buds at first then nice hopped bitterness. I like this beer because it reminded me of NBBCs Ranger line which is my favorite dept. store brew. A craft beer should stand out from the rest because of the premium price imho, and this beer did not. However, this beer could definitely be a door opener for people who like sweeter beers to turn a new leaf. I will buy this beer again and try others from the company. This beer is brewed from one company and sold by another and craft beer is a delicate process which takes close attention so brewers beware. Regards, AZZJ97
